<div class="row content">
  <div class="column side">
    <h2>Gyms?</h2>
    <p>You may be wondering how to get Pokecoins.  Pokecoins are obtainable when you place your pokemon in your local gym.  Depending on how long your pokemon stays in that gym without being knocked out, you will recieve that many pokecoins.  You can earn up to 50 pokecoins each day max, so be sure to strategically put pokemon in certain gyms.</p>
    <img src="http://www.pokemongomaniacs.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/take-over-pokemon-go-gym-1.jpg">
    
    
  </div>
  <div class="column middle">
    <h2>Pokecoins</h2>
    <p>When you put your pokemon in a gym, you may notice that when you get your pokemon back, you will recieve pokecoins.  Pokecoins are used for buying essential items to help you proceed to "be the very best".  For example, you can buy Lure modules, that attract the pokemon to you, or Egg incubators, that help you blastt your way through the impenetrable blockade of poke eggs overfilling your inventory.  Lucky eggs can be the very thing you need when you go on an evolving spree, evolving pokemon en masse to get to the next level.  Whatever you choose, be careful, you can also buy pokecoins with real money, but it's not really worth it in virtural land. </p>
    



